<document>
	<title>Trace element malabsorption in exocrine pancreatic insufficiency.</title>

	<author>Aggett-P-J.</author>
	<author>Thorn-J-M.</author>
	<author>Delves-H-T.</author>
	<author>Harries-J-T.</author>
	<author>Clayton-B-E.</author>

	<source>Monogr-Paediatr. 1979. 10. P 8-11.</source>

	<abstract>This paper presents preliminary results from metabolic balance
   studies of iron, zinc and manganese absorption and retention in
   children with cystic fibrosis and Shwachman&apos;s syndrome.
   Malabsorption of zinc, iron and manganese in exocrine pancreatic
   insufficiency has been demonstrated by these early studies.  A
   possible relationship between this and the associated features of CF
   has been briefly discussed, and indicates areas for further research.
   If such relationships are established then some form of trace element
   supplementation should be considered.</abstract>

